      "SummaryText": "the Alkylation Unit which involves both a toxic chemical, hydrofluoric acid and flammable mixtures including isobutane, butane, butylene, propylene and propane. The other refinery process units contain flammable compounds including hydrogen, methane, ethane, ethylene, propane, butane, isobutane, propylene, butylene, isopentane and normal pentane. The process units are divided into two process area blocks based on location within the refinery. The storage of liquefied petroleum gases (isobutane, butane, olefins and propane) is also a covered process.\n\n\n\nAccidental Release Prevention and Emergency Response\n\nCountryMark is committed to operating in a safe and environmentally sound manner while complying with governing laws, regulations and engineering standards.  This commitment is demonstrated through resources invested in safe design, operation and maintenance of the facility. CountryMark's operating practices and procedures ensure that numerous controls are implemented to prevent a release of toxic or flammable materials.\n\n\n\nIf a major release would occur, CountryMark has several layers of response that would be activated. Unit Operators are trained in initial responses to all types of potential incidents.  If warranted, the on-site Fire Brigade is called to provide the firefighting or emergency manpower requirements in the initial stages of a release. Next, a general community and industrial mutual aid fire response could be requested. Commercial emergency responders could also be obtained in addition to activation of all available emergency responders within a large radius of the refinery.\n\n\n\nGeneral Accidental Release Prevention Program\n\nCountryMark has a comprehensive program to prevent accidental releases of highly hazardous chemicals under the U.S. Occupational Safety and health Agency (OSHA) Process Safety Management (PSM) Program. The OSHA PSM program satisfies the EPA RMP requirements.  \n\n\n\nThere are many programs and procedures in place to prevent a chemic"
